# Admin Web theme is LOCKED

The Admin Web color system is **approved and frozen**. Do not redesign, retune, or refactor theme colors unless the user **explicitly** requests it.

## Status

- LOCKED
- APPROVED
- DO NOT MODIFY WITHOUT EXPLICIT USER APPROVAL

## Protected (do not change)

- Light mode palette
- Dark mode palette
- Theme tokens (`--vb-*`, `--palette-*`)
- Sidebar colors
- Header / topbar colors
- Page background colors
- Card / surface colors
- Button colors
- Accent colors
- Shadows, borders, and contrast values tied to the theme

Protected sources:

- `admin-web/src/theme/palette-colors.css`
- `admin-web/src/theme/admin-theme.css`
- `admin-web/src/theme/colors.ts`
- `admin-web/src/styles/admin-components.css` (color/shadow/border tokens only)
- Any admin-web component inline `style` colors or hardcoded `#` / `rgba()` values

## Required for all future Admin Web UI work

- Reuse existing theme tokens only
- Follow the approved color system
- Preserve visual consistency
- Never introduce new colors without explicit approval
- Never hardcode colors in components — use `--vb-*` variables

## Allowed without color approval

- Bug fixes (non-color)
- Layout, spacing, alignment
- Responsive fixes
- Accessibility fixes that do not change theme tokens (e.g. ARIA, focus order)
- Component improvements using existing tokens
- New screens/features styled with existing tokens

## Before any Admin Web color-related change

1. **Stop and warn the user** that the change affects the approved theme system.
2. **Do not proceed** until the user explicitly approves the color change.
3. Prefer token reuse over new values; prefer layout/structure fixes over color tweaks.

Treat the current Admin Web theme as the design baseline.
